"Marina di Andrea Gamba" is not her name. Instead it follows how Italians wrote names on records to signify, in this case, that Marina was the daughter of, at the time of the record, the living Andrea Gamba. Had Andrea been deceased, Marina's name on the record would show: "Marina fu Andrea Gamba", meaning "Marina, daughter of the deceased Andrea Gamba". By adding the father's name, the record is pointing out that Marina is a legitimate child, and therefore carries the father's surname Gamba.
